    "History": {
      "rows": [
        [
          "Staff Generated Concept",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "",
          "Created By:"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Staff Generated History"
        ],
        [
          "You were the second-born son of a moderately successful merchant family in Florence, Italy; and thus bound to enter the clergy while your younger brother went into the army and your elder brother inherited the family business. While most middle brothers would have envied the eldest, you would have switched places with your younger brother if you could. A life of quiet contemplation was not for you - nor was the indulgent lifestyle of the more corrupt Italian clergy. You preferred action, danger and the thrill of combat. And while you were sometimes allowed to train with your brother, at sixteen you entered the clergy. Fortunately, there was an order, unknown to you before then, which suited you perfectly: the Inquisition, an order within the Catholic Church dedicated to rooting out evil. You fought side by side with other ordained bishops and priests - even a nun or two. Your last fight came during a vampire war called the Anarch Revolt. Your team had reliable information that a very old vampire had taken up residence in a nearby monastery, and you had spent several months chipping away at its mortal base of power. Convinced the vampire was now powerless, you invaded - only to discover the entire mission was a trap. You alone survived to meet the monster in its lair, and were surprised by what you found. No fighting, but wine and chess laid out. You found yourself drawn into conversation with your target, an exceptionally beautiful woman who also had a solid education. You played chess with her and drank her wine, unable to lift a hand against her. You were certain she would kill you when she was done with you. And she did, in a manner of speaking. You awoke the next night a Cainite. Your sire was part of the newly-forming Sabbat, and you learned from her how to direct and manipulate mortals. You were a founder of the Order of St Blaise, and still have some influence in that faction. While you thought nothing would ever convince you to leave Montreal, finally, something has. You've learned that one of your former Inquisition members is not only a vampire like you, but that she has become the Camarilla Prince of Los Angeles. This intrigues you like nothing else ever could, and you must come watch."
        ],
        [
          "Sire:",
          "Melisande du Chartres",
          "Reference: (If any)",
          "",
          "",
          "Clan",
          "Toreador - Entranced by Art"
        ],
        [
          "Embrace Date:",
          "1497.0",
          "Embrace Location:",
          "Rome",
          "",
          "Generation",
          "Master Elder 7"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Who You Know",
          "Your relationship to these people is described. This may mean they do not know you."
        ],
        [
          "Isiah (NDC) (Mat Segal)",
          "The local member of the Order of St Blaise and someone to check up on."
        ],
        [
          "Vincent de Paul (Liliacea Lancers) (Michael Steinbach)",
          "The Archbishop of Los Angeles, you understand he is newly raised to the position after Don Guzman either left or was forced out (the rumors aren't clear, but he's now a Priscus, so he probably didn't fail). You understand the importance of courting power, and he would be the first person you'd want to cultivate - and evaluate him as a fit Cainite to lead the Sword of Caine in Los Angeles."
        ],
        [
          "Rafael de Corazon (Aleph Null) (Justin Benti)",
          "Another ancient like you. Though the Sabbat as a whole claims to not give credence to age, you understand that there are some things elders understand which the younger vampires simply don't, and it's good to have allies of an age with you."
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Starting Goals",
          "These are recomendations, not mandates."
        ],
        [
          "You had to give up much of your mortal influence when you left Montreal. Work to build your network back up (invest in Allies, Influence, Resources)."
        ],
        [
          "You'll have to find a pack. You bring a lot to the table, so don't entertain the first offer you get. Make sure that your pack understands how valuable a member you are, and that you can help each other rise."
        ],
        [
          "If anyone finds out that you used to be mortal Inquisition, it's going to be awkward for you. Build up your street cred so if the secret ever does come out, you can survive it."
        ],
        [
          "Find out more about Dafne Pictor - is it really her, and is she really the Prince of of Los Angeles? You know you can't make direct contact, but maybe a little monitoring? For the good of the Sword?"
        ],
        [],
        [
          "Player Amended History",
          "",
          "Date Submited"
        ]
      ],
